jobs.description:
A Podcast, where we unmask the people who are making tremendous strides in tech,
      
      yet whose stories are seldom heard. Link - https://www.mappingthejourney.com/

Senior software engineer in Identity group. 

Technologies used: Java, Spring, REST, Mockito, JUnit, JAAS
Authorization Framework: OAuth 2.0
Protocols: OpenID, OpenID Connect

Project: Reparo (Cloud Onboarding, Provisioning, Patching and Remediation tool)
      

    PayPal's cloud platform enables on-demand provisioning and deployment of
      infrastructure, applications and monitoring. I was part of PayPal's Cloud Team building
      
      tools to onboard and manage Cloud Infrastructure.

... See more

Project: McAfee SaaS Email Protection
Role: Software Engineer
Providing solutions to frequent spam attacks, adding new features to McAfee Email Protection product and constantly involved in solving issues related to Mail Transfer Agents. 
Technologies used: C++, Java, Redis, Memcache, Shell, Perl, Zabbix, Puppet and PHP

Project: Colorado Operations Resource Engine.
Role: Developer/Consultant
Description: I was part of the technical team and worked closely with client to design, develop and implement the conversion software to the new Java based application. During this time, I mapped all mainframe to Oracle table structures for both semi automated and automated conversion for the Advantage ERP application, including over 10 modules. Built tools in Java that help in migrating data from existing COFRS (Colorado Financial Reporting System) to CORE, developed crosswalks for conversion activities, including creation of tables and PDI maps, as well as executing data imports and managing crosswalk templates with the client.  
Technologies used: HTML, CSS, Java and XML

Project: Citsci Mobile App
Role: Software Developer
Description: This project aimed to develop a mobile app for the existing citsci.org website.  The app provides volunteers, scientists and participants to collect field data (observations) from remote places and upload the collected data to the server. Project aimed to replace the use of external GPS and paper questionnaires. 
Technologies used: Java, PHP and XML
GTA for the course Computer Security in Computer Science Department.

Project:  Place-based Climate Change Communication
Role: Software Development Engineer
Description: Project aimed at having a location-based climate change detection using repeat photography in southwest Alaskan national parks.  I had the responsibility of collecting requirements, design, architecture, coding, testing and deployment of the portal.  In addition, I was part of a development team in NREL responsible for developing many other NREL websites.
Responsibilities/Accomplishments:
â€¢	Database Design and UI Design with HTML and CSS
â€¢	Client side scripting with JavaScript and Jquery. 
â€¢	Server side development with PHP
Technologies used: PHP, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Jquery and SQL server
